    * trade-specific context, not office-worker context

14. Strategic Recommendations
* strongest angle inside the niche:
    * 40g+ job-site-safe no-microwave lunches for trades
* strongest buyer promise:
    * “Pack a real work lunch in 5–10 minutes that hits 40g+ protein, survives the workday safely, and costs less than eating out.”
* strongest product education angle:
    * teach a system, not recipes
* strongest trust-building mechanism:
    * food-safety transparency + cost math + labeled combo sheets
* strongest content-to-PDF bridge:
    * short-form videos that show one combo, one protein total, one cost, one safety label, then CTA to the full rotation/system PDF
* biggest warning signs:
    * vague health messaging
    * no cost breakdown
    * no worksite specificity
    * overpromising literal all-day no-cooling safety
* where the offer should become more specific:
    * make the buyer narrower in headlines
    * make the safety logic explicit
    * make the budget tiers visible
    * make the combo count concrete

